Aim:

  To study and analyze the common security vulnerabilities in an E-mail application.

Introduction:

  E-mail applications are used to send and receive messages over the internet.

  They can face many security problems if not properly protected.
  
  Studying these vulnerabilities helps to make e-mail systems more secure.

Common Vulnerabilities:

  Weak passwords make it easy for hackers to access accounts.

  No encryption allows attackers to read messages.
  
  Phishing emails trick users into giving personal information.
  
  Spam emails can spread viruses and malware.
  
  Fake sender addresses can be used to fool users.
  
  Insecure attachments may contain harmful files.
  
  Poor configuration may allow unauthorized access.
  
  Old software can have security holes.
  
  No logging makes it hard to detect attacks.
  
  Shared or public devices can leak login details.

Observation:

  E-mail applications are often attacked through phishing, weak passwords, or malware attachments.

Result:

  Different security vulnerabilities in e-mail applications were studied and understood.
